title: For Sale:  LAFAYETTE SCAMMER WITH COLTS and more LISTED........"UNREGISTERED USER"...
postcontent:
OBVIOUSLY something fishy is up with this chucklehead with the recently listed " Pre 70's Colt Commander 22mag" for $300???....Or a 1903 pocket "converted 25acp"???and a few others to note......

I already found the exact description and same photos of the "Commander 22mag" on gunsamerica, listed for $800+ and is a 45ACP, with exact same description that this scammer has copied and pasted but has somehow got 22mag in the caliber box. 

Also the AMT "1911 GOVERNMENT" Hand engraved.......AND THE 1903 COLT...all  under different "sellers" on gunsamerica....

ANYWAY, this is some serious bullshit, so be cautious! Let's keep our ARMSLIST free of this crap! 

Here is the responses I got when I questioned the listing...

1) "hello sorry it a mistake"

2) "hey are you here to question me or to buy hun i both sell on both side okay..  "

I also asked for another contact method or phone number (I'm just blunt like that) and I was answered with "dont let me show you who i am okay"

I COULD be wrong, but I am gonna take a stab and say this is a real SCAMMER. The texts suggest that whoever it is either cannot spell or make sentences, or is NOT a native english speaker. Regardless, veiled threats aside, NONE of us wants to get ripped off or see damage done to our gun site or our gun rights. Be safe out there all!

I have a 1943 Izhevsk Mosin-Nagant with round receiver.  I have done some light sanding (no more) on the sides of the trigger and it now has a reasonably smooth 5-pound pull.  Being a proper 1943, it has the half-gusset on the front sling strap mount and no gusset on the rear (things were pretty tough in Russia in 1943 and they were whipping these out as rapidly as possible with no frills).  

The rifle comes with all of the kit that comes with Mosins (strap, pouches, bayonet, bottle, tool kit) - see picture.
